trans-unit.source: Indicates whether the designated property of a Web Parts control is displayed in a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PropertyGridEditorPart"></xref> object.

The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PropertyGridEditorPart> control provides a generic user interface (UI) that enables users to edit custom properties on <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> and server controls placed in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartZoneBase> zones.
The editing UI is provided for properties that are marked in the source code with the `WebBrowsable` attribute (from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute> class).

When a property is marked with this attribute, a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PropertyGridEditorPart> control creates the editing UI based on the type of the property, and uses a <xref:System.ComponentModel.PropertyDescriptor> object if needed to convert the value in each editing control to the type of the property.

Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute"></xref> class with the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute.Browsable"></xref> property set to `true`.

The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute.%23ctor%2A> constructor is used when the `WebBrowsable` attribute is applied through the attribute declaration `[WebBrowsable()]` in C# or `<WebBrowsable()>` in Visual Basic.

Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute"></xref> class with the specified value for the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute.Browsable"></xref> property.
The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute.%23ctor%2A> constructor is used when the `WebBrowsable` attribute is applied through the attribute declaration with a Boolean value.

To prevent a property from being displayed in a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PropertyGridEditorPart> control, the property could be marked with the attribute `[WebBrowsable(false)]` in C# or `<WebBrowsable(false)>` in Visual Basic.
A Boolean value indicating whether the property should be displayed in a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PropertyGridEditorPart"></xref>.
Gets a value indicating whether a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PropertyGridEditorPart"></xref> control should display a specific property of a Web Parts control.
The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute.Browsable%2A> property is set through the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute.%23ctor%2A> constructor.
`true` if <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PropertyGridEditorPart"></xref> will display the property; otherwise, `false`.

Represents an instance of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute"></xref> class with the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute.Browsable"></xref> property set to the default value, which is `false`.

The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute.Default> field returns the same result as calling the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute.%23ctor%2A> constructor and passing `false` as the parameter.
Returns a value that indicates whether this instance is equal to a specified object.
An <xref href="System.Object"></xref> to compare with this instance, or `null`.
`true` if obj equals the type and value of this instance; otherwise, `false`.
Returns the hash code for the display name value.
A 32-bit signed integer hash code.
Determines whether the current instance is set to the default value.

`true` if the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute"></xref> equals <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute.Default"></xref>; otherwise, `false`.

Represents an instance of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute"></xref> class with the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute.Browsable"></xref> property set to `false`.

The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute.No> field returns the same result as calling the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute.%23ctor%2A> constructor and passing `false` as the parameter.

Represents an instance of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute"></xref> class with the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute.Browsable"></xref> property set to `true`.

The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute.Yes> field returns the same result as calling the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebBrowsableAttribute.%23ctor%2A> constructor and passing `true` as the parameter.
